 <h2>What to See at Dinosaur National Monument</h2>
<p>Dinosaur National Monument spans over 210,000 acres across the Utah-Colorado border. The main draw on the Utah side is the Quarry Exhibit Hall — 20 miles from our hotel — where you can see and touch over 1,500 dinosaur fossils still embedded in the rock face. Beyond the quarry, the monument offers stunning canyon overlooks, ancient Fremont-culture petroglyphs along the Cub Creek Road, and world-class whitewater rafting on the Green and Yampa rivers. There are no restaurants, gas stations, or stores inside the monument — Vernal is where you stock up.</p>
<ul class="feat-list">
 <li>Quarry Exhibit Hall — 1,500+ fossils in the rock wall</li>
 <li>Cub Creek petroglyphs — Fremont culture rock art</li>
 <li>Josie Bassett Morris cabin — homestead history</li>
